1
00:00:07,654 --> 00:00:10,616
HAENGBOK PAWNSHOP

2
00:00:10,699 --> 00:00:13,702
[crickets chirping]

3
00:00:25,047 --> 00:00:27,674
[♪ tense music]

4
00:00:47,861 --> 00:00:49,363
[exhales]

5
00:00:51,365 --> 00:00:52,574
[light clicks]

6
00:00:57,704 --> 00:00:59,081
What...

7
00:01:09,383 --> 00:01:10,550
Oh, shit.

8
00:01:12,719 --> 00:01:13,762
[gasps]

9
00:01:21,520 --> 00:01:22,521
Hey!

10
00:01:25,774 --> 00:01:26,900
Woogy, hey.

11
00:01:28,694 --> 00:01:30,570
Hey! Woogy!

12
00:01:31,571 --> 00:01:32,739
Wake up! Come on!

13
00:01:33,532 --> 00:01:34,783
[Heeju] Hey!

14
00:01:34,866 --> 00:01:36,535
[groans]

15
00:01:37,035 --> 00:01:38,954
Hey, what--what happened?
Why are you here?

16
00:01:39,037 --> 00:01:40,080
What the hell is going on?

17
00:01:40,163 --> 00:01:43,166
[groaning]

18
00:01:46,128 --> 00:01:47,129
Huh?

19
00:01:48,964 --> 00:01:50,674
Wh--What?

20
00:01:51,508 --> 00:01:53,510
-I asked you what you were doing here.
-[Woogy] I...

21
00:01:55,095 --> 00:01:57,431
The--the--the potatoes.

22
00:01:58,223 --> 00:01:59,641
[Woogy] The gold bars.

23
00:01:59,724 --> 00:02:01,268
Oh! Lee Dokyung! Oh!

24
00:02:02,060 --> 00:02:03,687
-What?
-[Woogy grunts]

25
00:02:03,770 --> 00:02:06,064
[groaning]

26
00:02:07,649 --> 00:02:09,526
[breathing heavily]

27
00:02:13,947 --> 00:02:14,948
I didn't do it.

28
00:02:15,866 --> 00:02:17,492
Seriously, I really didn't do it!

29
00:02:18,243 --> 00:02:19,703
[Woogy] Lee Dokyung showed up here and...

30
00:02:20,704 --> 00:02:23,165
He shot me.
Wait, I got shot.

31
00:02:23,248 --> 00:02:26,042
-[Heeju] Ah, shit.
[Woogy] Huh? How am I alive right now?

32
00:02:28,253 --> 00:02:30,088
Wait, what is this?

33
00:02:30,172 --> 00:02:32,382
-Where are the bars?
-[grunts]

34
00:02:33,300 --> 00:02:34,801
Heeju, I told you I didn't do anything.

35
00:02:36,219 --> 00:02:37,304
[Woogy] I really didn't take the gold!

36
00:02:37,387 --> 00:02:40,056
I mean, yeah, I came here to get it,
but then Lee Dokyung got to it.

37
00:02:40,557 --> 00:02:43,143
Wait, wait, wait!
What time is it?

38
00:02:43,226 --> 00:02:44,227
[Woogy gasps]

39
00:02:44,644 --> 00:02:45,645
-Come here!
-Huh?

40
00:02:45,729 --> 00:02:47,314
-[Woogy] No time to explain! Come on!
-[Heeju] What? Why?

41
00:02:47,397 --> 00:02:48,815
[door creaks open and shut]

42
00:02:49,691 --> 00:02:51,902
[both breathing heavily]

43
00:02:53,653 --> 00:02:55,655
[tires squealing]

44
00:02:56,865 --> 00:02:57,866
[Moonsu] Hey, go check it out.

45
00:03:00,869 --> 00:03:01,870
[Heeju] What?

46
00:03:02,412 --> 00:03:04,539
Heeju, my car.
Go to my car.

47
00:03:04,623 --> 00:03:06,708
-Let's go.
-[Woogy] We're clear!

48
00:03:16,259 --> 00:03:17,594
[car engine turns over]

49
00:03:17,677 --> 00:03:19,763
[tires scraping]

50
00:03:26,186 --> 00:03:27,604
[Woogy] By the way.

51
00:03:27,687 --> 00:03:29,397
How did you get away from Detective Kim?

52
00:03:30,857 --> 00:03:34,277
He let me go after
I gave him two gold bars.

53
00:03:34,361 --> 00:03:35,654
What? Really?

54
00:03:36,154 --> 00:03:37,948
A couple of gold bars and he lets you go?

55
00:03:38,031 --> 00:03:39,449
He didn't seem like that kinda guy.

56
00:03:41,117 --> 00:03:42,786
Well apparently he is.

57
00:03:42,911 --> 00:03:46,498
If I had kept my mouth shut until the end,
he wouldn't have even gotten that.

58
00:03:46,581 --> 00:03:48,500
[Woogy] I thought you were done
with Lee Dokyung, though.

59
00:03:48,583 --> 00:03:50,001
Why'd you tell him where the bars were?

60
00:03:52,921 --> 00:03:54,756
-[exhales]
-[Woogy] Oh, yeah.

61
00:03:59,511 --> 00:04:02,347
-Heeju. Here. Check this out.
-What is it?

62
00:04:02,430 --> 00:04:03,682
Huh? It's a dash cam.

63
00:04:04,641 --> 00:04:07,894
It must have caught that asshole
Lee Dokyung leaving the pawnshop.

64
00:04:08,436 --> 00:04:11,565
I mean, there's no way he just walked off
with all those gold bars on foot.

65
00:04:15,527 --> 00:04:17,028
[Woogy] What? Did you find something?

66
00:04:17,862 --> 00:04:18,989
Yeah.

67
00:04:19,072 --> 00:04:21,449
It looks like he's driving away in
a white car.

68
00:04:21,533 --> 00:04:23,952
[Woogy] Damn. I knew that asshole
would do this.

69
00:04:24,035 --> 00:04:25,996
How does it feel
to see his true colors?

70
00:04:26,913 --> 00:04:28,039
Pretty shitty, right?

71
00:04:32,419 --> 00:04:35,505
Okay. First thing we need to do
is find Lee Dokyung

72
00:04:35,589 --> 00:04:37,424
before he runs off with our gold bars.

73
00:04:38,717 --> 00:04:40,010
[Woogy exhales sharply]

74
00:04:44,639 --> 00:04:47,017
[Jinman] Right now I have Kim Heeju
here in custody.

75
00:04:47,767 --> 00:04:49,394
But I think I can release her.

76
00:04:50,145 --> 00:04:51,229
How about this?

77
00:04:52,063 --> 00:04:53,315
We should make a deal.
STYLE
::cue()

78
00:04:54,399 --> 00:04:55,483
[exhales]

79
00:05:11,875 --> 00:05:15,128
LUCKY JEWELRY WHOLESALE

80
00:05:29,643 --> 00:05:30,727
[grunts]

81
00:05:30,810 --> 00:05:32,729
Okay.

82
00:05:35,982 --> 00:05:39,945
So I heard you guys pay cash on
the spot here. Is that right?

83
00:05:40,028 --> 00:05:46,117
Uh, yeah, we do. Though, uh, it's going
to take a moment to get it ready.

84
00:05:46,201 --> 00:05:47,744
[Shop Keeper] It's quite a lot of money.

85
00:05:48,495 --> 00:05:49,496
How long?

86
00:05:49,579 --> 00:05:53,541
Uh, I'd say an hour.
Uh, maybe 30 minutes.

87
00:05:54,334 --> 00:05:56,586
-Please do it as fast as you can.
-[Shop Keeper] Yes, certainly.

88
00:05:56,670 --> 00:05:59,422
How about we get you
a cup of tea while you wait?

89
00:05:59,506 --> 00:06:00,799
Hey, Yeonju?

90
00:06:00,882 --> 00:06:03,051
Would you bring this gentleman
some tea, please?

91
00:06:03,134 --> 00:06:04,177
[Yeonju] Yes, sir.

92
00:06:25,657 --> 00:06:27,951
YES MONEY PRESIDENT KO GITAE
HE CAME.

93
00:06:28,034 --> 00:06:29,119
[Shop Keeper] He's here.

94
00:06:29,995 --> 00:06:30,996
[cell phone vibrates]

95
00:06:31,079 --> 00:06:32,914
Oh. He's there! He's there!

96
00:06:33,248 --> 00:06:35,083
This has to be Lee Dokyung, right?

97
00:06:36,209 --> 00:06:38,253
Kim Jinman wasn't bullshitting, huh?

98
00:06:39,170 --> 00:06:40,588
You had guys surround it, right?

99
00:06:40,672 --> 00:06:41,673
Yeah, of course.

100
00:06:41,756 --> 00:06:42,882
[Hocheol scoffs]

101
00:06:42,966 --> 00:06:43,967
[lighter flicks]

102
00:06:44,050 --> 00:06:45,051
Yeah, hey.

103
00:06:46,094 --> 00:06:47,929
Shut the place down
and keep that asshole inside.

104
00:06:48,013 --> 00:06:49,014
We'll be right over.

105
00:06:49,973 --> 00:06:51,015
Yeah, okay.

106
00:06:51,099 --> 00:06:52,392
[call drops]

107
00:06:52,684 --> 00:06:53,685
Come on.

108
00:06:59,357 --> 00:07:01,192
Who said you get to decide what we do?

109
00:07:02,068 --> 00:07:03,820
[Hocheol chuckles]

110
00:07:04,654 --> 00:07:05,947
[inhales on cigarette]

111
00:07:14,414 --> 00:07:17,041
So, uh, well, about the gold.

112
00:07:17,417 --> 00:07:19,794
You really sure you
wanna give Kim Jinman any?

113
00:07:19,878 --> 00:07:21,629
I mean, you're the one doing all the work.

114
00:07:22,881 --> 00:07:24,507
[Hocheol] Let's find the casket first.

115
00:07:24,591 --> 00:07:27,093
I'll need someone to clean up once
we take care of Chairman Ahn.

116
00:07:37,270 --> 00:07:39,314
[Yeonju] Hello. Welcome...

117
00:07:40,231 --> 00:07:42,442
[nervous breathing]

118
00:07:43,109 --> 00:07:45,069
[doors creaking]

119
00:07:47,614 --> 00:07:49,324
-Who the hell are--
-[blow lands]

120
00:07:49,407 --> 00:07:50,992
[all grunting]

121
00:08:09,260 --> 00:08:11,262
[phone trilling]
[Moonsu] Yes, boss.

122
00:08:11,346 --> 00:08:12,597
It's Lee Dokyung.

123
00:08:13,348 --> 00:08:14,557
Cool. Good work.

124
00:08:15,183 --> 00:08:16,184
[call drops]

125
00:08:16,267 --> 00:08:18,770
They checked his passport.
It's Lee Dokyung.

126
00:08:19,229 --> 00:08:20,855
Boss, we've finally found him!

127
00:08:20,939 --> 00:08:22,106
[laughs]

128
00:08:24,609 --> 00:08:26,820
[door creaking]

129
00:08:30,031 --> 00:08:31,032
Where's Lee Dokyung?

130
00:08:31,115 --> 00:08:32,242
[Henchman B] He's right over here, sir.

131
00:08:33,993 --> 00:08:36,871
[door creaks closed]

132
00:08:42,377 --> 00:08:45,380
[Gitae] Oh, man.
This wasn't necessary.

133
00:08:45,463 --> 00:08:46,464
Just hold still.

134
00:08:46,548 --> 00:08:48,341
[Dokyung breathing erratically]

135
00:08:48,424 --> 00:08:51,261
Captain. It's been a while.

136
00:08:53,763 --> 00:08:55,473
I was always gonna find you.

137
00:08:55,557 --> 00:08:57,642
There was really no need
for all the fuss.

138
00:08:59,727 --> 00:09:00,979
Where's the casket?

139
00:09:11,865 --> 00:09:14,325
[grunting]

140
00:09:15,410 --> 00:09:17,078
[groaning]

141
00:09:17,162 --> 00:09:19,122
[Dokyung breathing erratically]

142
00:09:19,747 --> 00:09:21,583
I--I don't know.

143
00:09:22,125 --> 00:09:24,586
Do you really mean that?
You don't know?

144
00:09:25,170 --> 00:09:26,588
Or you just don't feel like saying?

145
00:09:26,671 --> 00:09:29,757
Ah, shit.
I--I--I really don't know.

146
00:09:31,801 --> 00:09:33,011
Tell me who does.

147
00:09:34,804 --> 00:09:35,889
Kim Heeju?

148
00:09:36,431 --> 00:09:37,682
[scraping]

149
00:09:37,765 --> 00:09:38,850
[Hocheol] Tell me.

150
00:09:38,933 --> 00:09:40,185
[groaning]

151
00:09:40,685 --> 00:09:42,395
Before I peel your whole face off.

152
00:09:42,937 --> 00:09:45,940
[groaning]
STYLE
::cue()

153
00:09:48,193 --> 00:09:50,236
Heeju. Hee--Heeju.

154
00:09:51,070 --> 00:09:52,572
Heeju never told me where it is.

155
00:09:53,907 --> 00:09:55,074
I mean it.

156
00:09:57,410 --> 00:09:58,870
Well, that was fast.

157
00:09:59,621 --> 00:10:00,997
I haven't even started.

158
00:10:01,915 --> 00:10:03,583
[Dokyung whimpering]

159
00:10:04,542 --> 00:10:08,296
So Kim Heeju knows where it is,
but you claim you don't.

160
00:10:10,965 --> 00:10:12,634
Even though you're dating?

161
00:10:15,595 --> 00:10:17,305
Heeju doesn't trust me now.

162
00:10:18,932 --> 00:10:21,017
We broke up
and I can't even reach her anymore.

163
00:10:22,143 --> 00:10:23,144
Really?

164
00:10:24,604 --> 00:10:25,605
Bullshit.

165
00:10:28,775 --> 00:10:30,276
[breathing heavily]

166
00:10:33,321 --> 00:10:34,948
Why don't you call Kim Heeju, then?

167
00:10:36,532 --> 00:10:38,743
Call her and get her to come here.

168
00:10:40,161 --> 00:10:42,121
[Hocheol] Then maybe I'll spare your life,
Captain.

169
00:10:50,713 --> 00:10:53,716
[♪ sad piano music]

170
00:11:25,832 --> 00:11:28,835
[♪ music continues]

171
00:11:33,923 --> 00:11:38,136
EPISODE 10
GOLD LAND

172
00:11:38,219 --> 00:11:41,222
[blowtorch roaring]

173
00:11:45,435 --> 00:11:46,728
[exhales]

174
00:11:47,312 --> 00:11:49,939
[cell phone vibrating]

175
00:11:50,023 --> 00:11:51,024
[exhales sharply]

176
00:11:57,363 --> 00:11:58,364
INCOMING CALL

177
00:11:58,448 --> 00:11:59,699
[Woogy] Who is it? Detective Kim?

178
00:11:59,782 --> 00:12:00,950
No.

179
00:12:01,034 --> 00:12:02,493
[vibrating continues]

180
00:12:03,286 --> 00:12:04,620
It's Lee Dokyung.

181
00:12:06,289 --> 00:12:07,290
Lee Dokyung?

182
00:12:08,791 --> 00:12:10,960
You should pick up.
Find out where the gold bars are.

183
00:12:11,044 --> 00:12:12,920
Yeah, but he thinks I'm in custody,

184
00:12:13,004 --> 00:12:15,506
so he would expect Detective Kim
to answer.

185
00:12:16,424 --> 00:12:21,387
But then if he's expecting Detective Kim,
then why would he even try to call me?

186
00:12:22,263 --> 00:12:23,264
[exhales]

187
00:12:23,348 --> 00:12:24,766
I--it doesn't matter.
Just pick up.

188
00:12:28,186 --> 00:12:29,187
[Dokyung] Hey Heeju.

189
00:12:30,396 --> 00:12:32,690
I'm at Lucky Jewelry
in Daejeong right now.

190
00:12:34,359 --> 00:12:38,196
I'm looking at some wedding rings for us.
Can you come over here?

191
00:12:39,280 --> 00:12:40,281
Huh?

192
00:12:41,074 --> 00:12:42,116
What do you mean?

193
00:12:42,700 --> 00:12:43,701
[Dokyung] Heeju!

194
00:12:45,787 --> 00:12:47,455
How are you able to answer the phone?

195
00:12:50,958 --> 00:12:53,753
Heeju, don't come here no matter what!
You hear me? Heeju!

196
00:12:53,836 --> 00:12:55,797
-I'll get right to the point, Kim Heeju.
-[Dokyung struggling]

197
00:12:55,880 --> 00:12:56,881
Where is the casket?

198
00:12:58,383 --> 00:13:00,802
[Hocheol] If you tell me right now,
I'll spare Lee Dokyung's life.

199
00:13:01,552 --> 00:13:02,929
But I'll kill him if you don't.

200
00:13:03,012 --> 00:13:04,972
[muffled groaning]

201
00:13:05,056 --> 00:13:07,683
[Heeju] Cha Yujin told you where it was
and you still killed her anyway.

202
00:13:08,184 --> 00:13:09,310
You're right.

203
00:13:10,269 --> 00:13:11,479
[exhales]

204
00:13:13,898 --> 00:13:15,233
What should I do?

205
00:13:16,442 --> 00:13:18,903
I really would like the captain to live.

206
00:13:20,113 --> 00:13:21,447
[Woogy exhales]

207
00:13:23,074 --> 00:13:24,742
What if I bring the casket to you?

208
00:13:25,660 --> 00:13:26,702
[Hocheol] Really?

209
00:13:27,412 --> 00:13:29,330
Yeah, I'll give you the casket.
I really will.

210
00:13:29,831 --> 00:13:31,124
So please let him go.

211
00:13:32,041 --> 00:13:34,710
-[Hocheol] Yeah. Yeah, of course.
-[muffled shouting]

212
00:13:35,378 --> 00:13:36,796
Uh, what time can I meet you?

213
00:13:36,879 --> 00:13:38,172
You're in Jeongsan, right?

214
00:13:38,714 --> 00:13:40,925
So then let me think.
Two, three hours...

215
00:13:41,467 --> 00:13:42,552
[Hocheol] Let's meet around midnight.

216
00:13:43,094 --> 00:13:44,178
Okay.

217
00:13:44,262 --> 00:13:45,680
[Hocheol] If you don't show up
by midnight...

218
00:13:46,264 --> 00:13:48,516
...I'll skin Lee Dokyung alive.

219
00:13:49,517 --> 00:13:50,518
[phone disconnects]

220
00:13:51,018 --> 00:13:52,061
[Woogy] Heeju.

221
00:13:54,188 --> 00:13:55,398
Why would you tell him that?

222
00:13:56,482 --> 00:13:57,525
Huh?

223
00:13:57,608 --> 00:14:00,194
[Woogy] Heeju!
You need to wake up.

224
00:14:00,278 --> 00:14:02,446
Seriously, Lee Dokyung stabbed you in
the back and took all

225
00:14:02,530 --> 00:14:04,157
of the gold bars for himself.

226
00:14:04,240 --> 00:14:05,533
And he shot me, too!

227
00:14:06,450 --> 00:14:08,411
[Woogy] We shouldn't be worried whether
Lee Dokyung lives or dies.

228
00:14:08,494 --> 00:14:10,413
We need to worry about saving ourselves!

229
00:14:13,040 --> 00:14:15,084
How long would it take to get
to Daejong from here?

230
00:14:16,836 --> 00:14:19,172
I don't know.
Hour and a half, if we're fast.

231
00:14:21,299 --> 00:14:23,926
Lee Dokyung must have parked
the car close to Lucky Jewelry.

232
00:14:25,136 --> 00:14:27,638
And Park said he'd keep him alive
until midnight.

233
00:14:28,264 --> 00:14:30,850
So all we have to do is find where
he parked the car by then.

234
00:14:31,851 --> 00:14:33,394
The gold bars have to be in there.

235
00:14:33,477 --> 00:14:35,563
Oh. Okay.

236
00:14:36,355 --> 00:14:38,107
[Woogy] Let's go, then.
I'll pull the car around.
STYLE
::cue()

237
00:14:40,943 --> 00:14:43,654
[crickets chirping]

238
00:14:50,536 --> 00:14:51,579
[inhales]

239
00:14:52,914 --> 00:14:55,583
[long exhale]

240
00:15:02,089 --> 00:15:04,592
[exhales]

241
00:15:22,276 --> 00:15:25,279
[car engine rumbling]

242
00:15:26,030 --> 00:15:27,281
[car parks]

243
00:15:27,365 --> 00:15:30,993
Lucky Jewelry is on
the back street over there.

244
00:15:31,077 --> 00:15:33,913
There's no room to park there, though,
so he must have parked around here.

245
00:15:35,456 --> 00:15:37,750
You check the streets over there.
I'll go that way.

246
00:15:39,001 --> 00:15:40,127
We're not going together?

247
00:15:40,920 --> 00:15:42,255
We don't have time for that.

248
00:15:43,839 --> 00:15:44,840
[Woogy] Heeju.

249
00:15:45,967 --> 00:15:48,886
If one of us gets captured by Yes Money...

250
00:15:49,804 --> 00:15:52,306
...let's save the other even if we have
to give up the gold.

251
00:15:53,391 --> 00:15:54,642
I won't agree to that.

252
00:15:55,685 --> 00:15:56,769
No.

253
00:15:56,852 --> 00:15:59,021
I don't want to live if we have
to give up the gold.

254
00:15:59,105 --> 00:16:01,399
I don't.
I'd rather just die.

255
00:16:03,359 --> 00:16:05,236
I'd still feel the same
if you got caught.

256
00:16:08,197 --> 00:16:09,198
Okay.

257
