779
00:49:19,770 --> 00:49:21,480
One is mine.
Chairman Ahn knows.

780
00:49:25,192 --> 00:49:26,944
[gold bars clinking]

781
00:49:27,027 --> 00:49:29,780
[Heeju breathing heavily]

782
00:49:30,739 --> 00:49:33,242
Keep going straight
and you'll see Woogy's car.

783
00:49:33,325 --> 00:49:34,326
Get moving. Go on.

784
00:49:34,952 --> 00:49:35,953
Wait, what about you?

785
00:49:37,371 --> 00:49:38,622
What do you mean?

786
00:49:39,290 --> 00:49:40,958
Aren't you going, too?

787
00:49:41,959 --> 00:49:43,669
I can take care of myself.

788
00:49:44,587 --> 00:49:46,880
Hurry up. It's straight ahead. Go.

789
00:49:48,090 --> 00:49:50,217
[inhales]

790
00:49:51,385 --> 00:49:53,637
[scraping]

791
00:49:56,849 --> 00:49:58,851
Go on! Go!

792
00:50:13,115 --> 00:50:14,658
What?

793
00:50:15,200 --> 00:50:18,203
[labored breathing]

794
00:50:18,454 --> 00:50:20,331
[scraping]

795
00:50:21,957 --> 00:50:24,126
What the fuck?

796
00:50:26,795 --> 00:50:28,964
[gold bars clinking]

797
00:50:38,140 --> 00:50:41,143
[car engine revving]

798
00:50:44,355 --> 00:50:45,898
[bars clinking]

799
00:50:45,981 --> 00:50:47,358
[Mr. Jang groans]

800
00:50:51,236 --> 00:50:52,404
[clinking]

801
00:50:52,488 --> 00:50:55,366
[Mr. Jang grunting]

802
00:50:56,533 --> 00:50:58,369
They're fake. Fuck.

803
00:50:58,452 --> 00:51:00,871
-This shit is fake, sir!
-What the hell?

804
00:51:01,789 --> 00:51:02,790
[Geumseong Henchman D] Ah, fuck!

805
00:51:02,873 --> 00:51:03,874
[groans]

806
00:51:03,957 --> 00:51:06,335
Why are you standing around? Go!

807
00:51:06,418 --> 00:51:07,544
[groans]

808
00:51:10,339 --> 00:51:11,340
[yelps]

809
00:51:11,423 --> 00:51:12,424
[clangs]

810
00:51:13,884 --> 00:51:14,927
[both grunting]

811
00:51:16,345 --> 00:51:17,638
[thunks]
Ow!

812
00:51:19,390 --> 00:51:20,724
[both grunting]

813
00:51:21,558 --> 00:51:22,810
[blow lands]
[groans]

814
00:51:23,560 --> 00:51:25,688
[Jinman breathing heavily]

815
00:51:26,438 --> 00:51:28,273
[groaning]

816
00:51:31,902 --> 00:51:34,446
[Chairman Ahn] Hurry up and get Kim Heeju!

817
00:51:34,530 --> 00:51:36,115
[car engine turns over]

818
00:51:36,824 --> 00:51:38,951
[Jinman grunting]

819
00:51:39,910 --> 00:51:41,620
[engine revving]

820
00:51:42,371 --> 00:51:43,455
[glass shatters]

821
00:51:43,539 --> 00:51:45,165
[crashing]

822
00:51:47,292 --> 00:51:48,961
[engine revving]

823
00:51:49,044 --> 00:51:50,462
[bangs]

824
00:52:02,766 --> 00:52:05,769
[groaning]

825
00:52:28,625 --> 00:52:29,626
[Sunok] Let...

826
00:52:30,127 --> 00:52:33,881
Let her live the way she wants to.

827
00:52:34,840 --> 00:52:40,721
[Sunok] Let her go her own way.

828
00:52:40,804 --> 00:52:41,847
I just want...

829
00:52:41,930 --> 00:52:45,517
[groaning]

830
00:52:45,601 --> 00:52:47,352
...to live a normal life.

831
00:52:47,436 --> 00:52:50,439
[labored breathing]

832
00:52:50,522 --> 00:52:53,984
Just a--just a normal life.

833
00:52:55,027 --> 00:52:56,153
[exhales]

834
00:52:57,196 --> 00:53:00,199
[labored breathing]

835
00:53:14,213 --> 00:53:15,339
[gunshot]
STYLE
::cue()

836
00:53:18,967 --> 00:53:21,512
[crickets chirping]

837
00:53:21,595 --> 00:53:24,223
There aren't any cars chasing us, right?

838
00:53:24,306 --> 00:53:26,683
We did it.
Heeju, we made it out.

839
00:53:26,767 --> 00:53:29,311
[both breathing heavily]

840
00:53:31,230 --> 00:53:32,523
The detective?

841
00:53:33,023 --> 00:53:34,274
[Woogy] Huh?

842
00:53:34,358 --> 00:53:35,484
Detective Kim?

843
00:53:35,567 --> 00:53:37,945
Oh, I think he drove the other direction.

844
00:53:38,028 --> 00:53:39,321
That's what we had planned.

845
00:53:41,406 --> 00:53:43,492
JEONGSAN POLICE STATION
DETECTIVE KIM JINMAN

846
00:53:43,575 --> 00:53:45,202
CALLING... JEONGSAN POLICE STATION
DETECTIVE KIM JINMAN

847
00:53:45,285 --> 00:53:46,912
Wait, are you calling him?
No, no, no, no, Heeju.

848
00:53:46,995 --> 00:53:48,080
[Heeju exhales]

849
00:53:48,163 --> 00:53:49,873
No need for that.
He'll call us later.

850
00:53:51,416 --> 00:53:52,543
That thing down there...

851
00:53:53,669 --> 00:53:54,795
...he told me to give it to you.

852
00:53:57,548 --> 00:53:59,007
And look in the glove box, too.

853
00:54:01,426 --> 00:54:02,511
[groans]

854
00:54:02,594 --> 00:54:03,637
[Woogy] There's a gun in there.

855
00:54:04,596 --> 00:54:06,139
You should take it just in case.

856
00:54:12,187 --> 00:54:13,188
[glove compartment closes]

857
00:54:13,564 --> 00:54:15,732
So we need to load the bars before
we head to Mokcheon.

858
00:54:16,900 --> 00:54:17,901
[Woogy] Where are they?

859
00:54:18,902 --> 00:54:21,363
Huh? Are they already
at Mokcheon Port, then?

860
00:54:23,073 --> 00:54:25,325
Or are they still in Jeongsan?

861
00:54:27,536 --> 00:54:28,662
[gun cocks]

862
00:54:28,745 --> 00:54:30,038
Stop the car.

863
00:54:33,709 --> 00:54:34,710
[Woogy] Heeju.

864
00:54:36,837 --> 00:54:37,838
Pull over.

865
00:54:44,136 --> 00:54:47,139
[car engine rumbling]

866
00:54:52,144 --> 00:54:53,228
Now get out.

867
00:54:55,272 --> 00:54:56,273
Heeju.

868
00:54:57,482 --> 00:54:58,525
Don't do this.

869
00:55:00,485 --> 00:55:02,779
I'm sorry, Woogy, but...

870
00:55:03,905 --> 00:55:05,616
...you shouldn't know where
the gold bars are.

871
00:55:08,910 --> 00:55:10,120
[Heeju] If it weren't for you...

872
00:55:11,538 --> 00:55:13,832
...I know there's no way I would have made
it this far.

873
00:55:15,709 --> 00:55:17,919
But you never know.
People can always change.

874
00:55:19,212 --> 00:55:20,964
I'm not gonna steal the gold, Heeju.

875
00:55:21,798 --> 00:55:22,883
[Heeju] I believe you.

876
00:55:24,217 --> 00:55:27,846
I really do trust you but there's still
a small chance that you could change.

877
00:55:39,733 --> 00:55:40,901
[car door closes]

878
00:55:43,487 --> 00:55:44,946
[Heeju grunts]

879
00:55:48,325 --> 00:55:51,328
[engine revving]

880
00:55:52,287 --> 00:55:55,290
[♪ sad music]

881
00:56:03,757 --> 00:56:04,800
Goodbye...

882
00:56:06,259 --> 00:56:07,260
...Heeju.

883
00:56:09,513 --> 00:56:12,766
JEONGSAN CENTRAL CHURCH

884
00:56:17,521 --> 00:56:20,524
[engine rumbling]

885
00:56:23,902 --> 00:56:24,903
[car parks]

886
00:56:24,986 --> 00:56:26,363
[Heeju exhales sharply]

887
00:56:27,781 --> 00:56:30,075
[groaning]

888
00:56:31,201 --> 00:56:34,204
[gasping]

889
00:56:39,042 --> 00:56:40,043
[exhales sharply]

890
00:56:40,127 --> 00:56:43,130
[Heeju breathing heavily]
STYLE
::cue()

891
00:56:48,385 --> 00:56:49,678
[zipper unzips]

892
00:56:54,433 --> 00:56:55,434
[gold clinks]

893
00:56:55,517 --> 00:56:57,394
[Heeju groans]

894
00:57:07,654 --> 00:57:09,239
[zipper zips]

895
00:57:09,322 --> 00:57:12,325
[breathing heavily]

896
00:57:21,168 --> 00:57:24,171
[breathing erratically]

897
00:57:26,965 --> 00:57:28,550
[groans]

898
00:57:29,801 --> 00:57:32,804
[wincing]

899
00:57:33,305 --> 00:57:35,265
[inhales sharply]

900
00:57:35,348 --> 00:57:36,641
[pained exhale]

901
00:57:43,273 --> 00:57:44,566
[exhales]

902
00:57:48,278 --> 00:57:49,404
[Heeju groans]

903
00:57:51,364 --> 00:57:54,367
[labored breathing]

904
00:58:18,809 --> 00:58:20,060
[Heeju groans]

905
00:58:27,317 --> 00:58:29,277
Looks like you made it just in time.

906
00:58:30,278 --> 00:58:31,947
[Donggu] Wait, are you alone?

907
00:58:32,906 --> 00:58:34,449
That man isn't going with you?

908
00:58:36,743 --> 00:58:37,828
I'm going alone.

909
00:58:42,457 --> 00:58:45,168
You know how it works. Money.

910
00:58:48,797 --> 00:58:49,881
[both grunt]

911
00:58:51,508 --> 00:58:52,759
There's a gold bar.

912
00:58:53,969 --> 00:58:55,136
Ten kilograms.

913
00:58:56,847 --> 00:58:58,974
It's worth about 1.5 billion won.

914
00:59:09,693 --> 00:59:12,696
[engine rumbling]

915
00:59:21,454 --> 00:59:24,457
[shallow breathing]

916
00:59:24,541 --> 00:59:27,544
[♪ sad music continues]

917
00:59:55,488 --> 00:59:58,491
[boat horns blaring]

918
01:00:06,082 --> 01:00:09,085
[rumbling and creaking]

919
01:00:09,169 --> 01:00:12,172
[light buzzing]
STYLE
::cue()

920
01:00:25,352 --> 01:00:26,728
[exhales]

921
01:00:40,075 --> 01:00:41,368
[groans]

922
01:00:46,247 --> 01:00:47,374
[grunts]

923
01:00:47,916 --> 01:00:49,042
[exhales]

924
01:00:50,377 --> 01:00:51,503
[grunts]

925
01:01:26,871 --> 01:01:33,878
THE LATE YEO SUNOK
DATE OF DEATH: SEPTEMBER 28, 2026

926
01:01:41,219 --> 01:01:44,222
[♪ sad music]

927
01:01:52,355 --> 01:01:55,358
[shuddering]

928
01:01:57,736 --> 01:01:59,821
Mom. Oh, Mom.

929
01:01:59,904 --> 01:02:02,532
[whimpering]

930
01:02:02,615 --> 01:02:03,742
Mom!

931
01:02:11,916 --> 01:02:14,919
[crying]

932
01:02:25,889 --> 01:02:27,599
[clanging]

933
01:02:31,644 --> 01:02:34,647
[urn rattling]

934
01:02:36,191 --> 01:02:39,194
[clanging continues]

935
01:03:09,599 --> 01:03:12,602
[♪ music continues]

936
01:03:19,943 --> 01:03:22,946
[crying quietly]

937
01:03:23,029 --> 01:03:26,032
[lights buzzing]
STYLE
::cue()

938
01:03:40,130 --> 01:03:43,133
[birds chirping]

939
01:03:59,858 --> 01:04:02,902
-How much is it?
-That would be four euros, please.

940
01:04:04,320 --> 01:04:06,114
-Thank you.
-[Fruit Vendor] Thank you very much.

941
01:04:09,826 --> 01:04:12,162
[Shopkeeper] Haran, how are you?

942
01:04:12,245 --> 01:04:14,622
That outfit looks great on you.

943
01:04:14,706 --> 01:04:17,292
Thank you. Thanks to you.

944
01:04:18,084 --> 01:04:20,003
You should come by next week again.
We'll have lots of new items.

945
01:04:20,086 --> 01:04:21,087
Yeah, okay.

946
01:04:24,799 --> 01:04:27,802
[♪ melancholy piano music]

947
01:04:29,888 --> 01:04:31,181
Hello.

948
01:04:31,264 --> 01:04:33,474
Come on in.
How have you been? Good?

949
01:04:33,558 --> 01:04:34,642
Yes, of course.

950
01:04:35,852 --> 01:04:37,979
Choose anything you want.
I'll pack the bread for you.

951
01:04:39,022 --> 01:04:43,610
The olive oil you gave me
the other day was amazing.

952
01:04:44,944 --> 01:04:48,615
I'll tell my wife that Ms. Ju liked
the olive oil. She'll love it.

953
01:04:48,698 --> 01:04:49,949
Yes.

954
01:04:50,033 --> 01:04:51,951
Wait, I have something for you.
Give me a second.

955
01:04:57,415 --> 01:04:59,751
I put it inside and then forgot about it.

956
01:05:01,002 --> 01:05:03,171
I should be talking less at my age.

957
01:05:03,671 --> 01:05:05,215
If I were a wise old man,
I would've known how.

958
01:05:07,133 --> 01:05:08,927
Can you carry this home?

959
01:05:09,010 --> 01:05:10,178
Of course.

960
01:05:10,511 --> 01:05:12,013
Great. Perfect.

961
01:05:12,597 --> 01:05:14,140
Thank you so much.

962
01:05:14,599 --> 01:05:20,521
No problem. Anytime for a beautiful
and kind person like you.

963
01:05:21,606 --> 01:05:22,982
-Thank you.
-[Baker] Bye. Thank you.

964
01:05:24,067 --> 01:05:26,527
Hello. What a cute family.
How have you been?

965
01:05:38,831 --> 01:05:41,834
[car rumbling]

966
01:05:44,295 --> 01:05:46,798
[engine humming]

967
01:05:50,802 --> 01:05:53,805
[gate doors clacking]

968
01:06:24,919 --> 01:06:27,922
[blade slicing]

969
01:06:44,272 --> 01:06:46,107
[urn clinking]
STYLE
::cue()

970
01:07:13,843 --> 01:07:15,428
[lighter flicking]

971
01:07:15,511 --> 01:07:20,391
THE LATE YEO SUNOK

972
01:07:20,475 --> 01:07:27,482
THE LATE KIM JINMAN

973
01:07:31,069 --> 01:07:34,280
I RECEIVED THE WINE ALL RIGHT.
HOW ABOUT YOU?

974
01:07:46,334 --> 01:07:49,337
[birds chirping]

975
01:08:39,387 --> 01:08:40,388
[light clicks]

976
01:08:40,471 --> 01:08:43,474
[♪ melancholy music]

977
01:08:43,558 --> 01:08:46,561
[birds chirping]

978
01:09:02,952 --> 01:09:04,078
[Woogy] Hey!

979
01:09:05,204 --> 01:09:06,289
Bonjour!

980
01:09:10,209 --> 01:09:12,670
Ah, shit.

981
01:09:15,256 --> 01:09:17,425
[Woogy] Man, that was a long way, huh?

982
01:09:17,508 --> 01:09:18,926
[Woogy chuckles]

983
01:09:27,727 --> 01:09:28,769
You made it.

984
01:09:33,149 --> 01:09:34,150
You made it.

985
01:09:36,444 --> 01:09:37,445
[scoffs]

986
01:09:53,252 --> 01:09:54,253
[Woogy chuckles]

987
01:10:01,302 --> 01:10:03,304
Holy shit.
How big is this place?

988
01:10:08,935 --> 01:10:10,311
[Woogy exhales]

989
01:10:12,647 --> 01:10:13,940
[Woogy] This is insane, right?

990
01:10:15,817 --> 01:10:16,818
[lighter flicking]

991
01:10:16,901 --> 01:10:17,985
[Woogy] Look at this!

992
01:10:21,405 --> 01:10:24,659
[Woogy] Is there a place like this
I could snag? Huh?

993
01:10:24,742 --> 01:10:27,703
-[Heeju] I don't think you can live here.
-[Woogy] Ah, why not?

994
01:10:27,787 --> 01:10:30,081
[Heeju] Just have your wine
and enjoy your time.

995
01:10:30,164 --> 01:10:33,167
[♪ dramatic music]
STYLE
::cue()

996
01:10:59,485 --> 01:11:06,492
THE BAKER'S WIFE

997
01:11:07,368 --> 01:11:10,788
Here's your bread, Miss Pretty Hat.

998
01:11:11,747 --> 01:11:14,750
[Baker] There's a lot of sweetness
inside this bread.

999
01:11:14,834 --> 01:11:17,753
-[Customer] Thank you. I'll come again.
-[Baker] Thank you. Goodbye.

1000
01:11:19,589 --> 01:11:20,798
Hello.

1001
01:11:25,303 --> 01:11:26,679
It looks delicious.

1002
01:11:27,597 --> 01:11:29,974
Once you try it, you'll want
to come back the next day.

1003
01:11:34,270 --> 01:11:35,396
By the way...

1004
01:11:36,355 --> 01:11:37,857
The young Asian woman.

1005
01:11:38,149 --> 01:11:40,526
She's a little short
and her name is Ju Haran.

1006
01:11:41,777 --> 01:11:48,784
It seems like she comes here
every now and then.

1007
01:11:49,118 --> 01:11:51,203
[Baker] Uh...

1008
01:11:51,287 --> 01:11:52,413
I'm not sure.

1009
01:11:52,872 --> 01:11:56,000
There are a lot
of Asian tourists coming here.

1010
01:11:56,542 --> 01:11:57,793
I'm sorry,

1011
01:11:57,877 --> 01:11:59,045
but we've been getting more

1012
01:11:59,128 --> 01:12:00,421
and more young Asian
customers like you,

1013
01:12:00,504 --> 01:12:02,340
coming here after hearing
about our bread.

1014
01:12:03,049 --> 01:12:06,302
So I can't remember
every single one of them.

1015
01:12:12,558 --> 01:12:13,893
All right.

1016
01:12:14,810 --> 01:12:15,895
Thank you.

1017
01:12:16,729 --> 01:12:19,732
[♪ dramatic music]

1018
01:12:47,802 --> 01:12:50,805
[♪ music continues]

1019
01:13:17,832 --> 01:13:20,835
[♪ music continues]

